{"title":"Siracusa on Mac OS X at 20","link":"https://twitter.com/siracusa/status/1374748598261415939","date":1616635553000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section aria-labelledby=\"accessible-list-0\" role=\"region\"><h2 aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"auto\" role=\"heading\" id=\"accessible-list-0\">Conversation</h2><div aria-label=\"Timeline: Conversation\"><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\" data-focusvisible-polyfill=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"tweet-promoted-label conversation-level-label tweet-social-context tweet-user-name tweet-user-screen-name tweet-user-label tweet-timestamp tweet-reply-context tweet-text tweet-rich-content-label conversation-control-label tweet-action-buttons\"><div><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/siracusa\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1501070030/John_2011_1_500x500_normal.png\"></p></div></a></div><div lang=\"en\" dir=\"auto\" id=\"tweet-text\"><p><span>Today is the 20th anniversary of the release of Mac OS X 10.0. If you'd like to look back at my writing on the subject, here's a collection of links: </span><a dir=\"ltr\" href=\"https://t.co/Y6oDKND8wN?amp=1\" target=\"_blank\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\" rel=\" noopener noreferrer\">hypercritical.co/2015/04/15/os-</a></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/siracusa\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1501070030/John_2011_1_500x500_normal.png\"></p></div></a></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/siracusa\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1501070030/John_2011_1_500x500_normal.png\"></p></div></a></div><div><div><p><span>You really had to be there…</span></p></div><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/siracusa/status/1374772021503070217/photo/1\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"Apple's original public &quot;theme&quot; image fot the Aqua user interface: a translucent blue lozenge-stye button with the word &quot;AQUA&quot; in it.\" data-testid=\"tweetPhoto\"><p><img alt=\"Apple's original public &quot;theme&quot; image fot the Aqua user interface: a translucent blue lozenge-stye button with the word &quot;AQUA&quot; in it.\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/media/ExQr3axXEAA7aFO?format=png&amp;name=small\"></p></div></a></div></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/neqone\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1062350884414218241/ojfrcGeo_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>I hate to admit how many times I go back and read the reviews of the DP and PB releases if nothing then just for the screenshots. I didn't get my hands on it until PB but I was so excited for it back in the day :).</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/slaine_\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1016972749158285313/vCgmoz19_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>I'm the same. It was a very exciting time, watching the development from Rhapsody through Mac OS X Server to Mac OS X releases.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/johan_malmstrom\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1114041923927306241/OQXhCGS0_normal.png\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>Put things in perspective. I only used “classic” Mac OS for 15yrs.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/slaine_\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1016972749158285313/vCgmoz19_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div lang=\"en\" dir=\"auto\"><p><span>Those articles convinced me to go Mac after being a Mac user wannabe, even during the dark times. Also introduced me to</span></p><p><span>as I found those articles first.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/connormw\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1165863166389211142/R22QjEjW_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>It took nearly 20 years, but finally the \"ten\" versus \"X\" argument is no longer!</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/adhess\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1289250346469122049/RTqlsEuk_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>Funny I still think of it as the \"new\" MacOS. 20 years ... and more than 30 since NeXTStep launched.</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Josephzoller\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/915990643230601216/eZj_Z6dG_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>\"Mac OS X likes RAM. The official requirement is a minimum of 128.. Some people will tell you that you can get by with 64.. And, in fact, you can. I'll bet you could even boot OS X with as little as 32 if you were persistent enough. But merely \"booting\" is a far cry from \"using.\"</span></p></div></div></article></div><div><article role=\"article\" data-focusable=\"true\" tabindex=\"0\"><div data-testid=\"tweet\"><div><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Josephzoller\" role=\"link\" data-focusable=\"true\"><div aria-label=\"\"><p><img alt=\"\" draggable=\"true\" src=\"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/915990643230601216/eZj_Z6dG_normal.jpg\"></p></div></a></div><div><p><span>If I remember, \"using\" anything in 10.0 with any amount of ram was debatable. Wasn't the main selling point for each of the first 2-3 versions, \"we made it faster\"?</span></p></div></div></article></div></div></section></div>","author":"John Gruber","siteTitle":"Daring Fireball","siteHash":"fc569638025dadf22a867470f8215f38855cf50e975782a6c989909474292a36","entryHash":"3bb87b8a64235aa86cf7dd0a545681bb719a22de35b34448b8cb62ca6721be75","category":"Tech"}